RIYADH: A delegation from the Quality of Life Program (QLP) has visited Dareen Palace, Tarout Castle, Tarout Heritage Coffee and the waterfront in Dammam, which is one of the projects to be implemented in the Eastern Region, Saudi Press Agency (SPA) reported. The QLP is one of the insitutions instigated across Saudi Arabia to achieve the Kingdom’s Vision 2030. The Executive Director of the Implementation Support Sector and the Acting Chief Marketing and Communication Officer at the Quality of Life Program Center, Khalid bin Abdullah Al-Bakr, stressed the importance of these projects, which will be carried out by the Ministry of Municipal and Rural Affairs and Housing and the Sharqia Development Authority. The projects aim to maintain heritage, improve the environment, activating tourist and cultural attractions, as well as creating a cultural tourist destination in the region. The projects will provide various promising investment opportunities in the region, benefiting residents, tourists, and visitors, in addition to the private sector.